## Features Engineered

| Category | Features |
|----------|----------|
| Calendar | Year, Month, Day, WeekOfYear, DayOfYear, Quarter |
| Business Calendar | IsWeekend, IsMonthStart, IsMonthEnd |
| Lag Features | Sales_Lag_7, Sales_Lag_14, Sales_Lag_28 |
| Rolling Mean | Sales_Rolling_Mean_7, 14, 28 |
| Rolling Std | Sales_Rolling_Std_7, 14, 28 |
| Promotion | Promo, PromoRunLength, PromoYesterday, Promo2 |
| Store | StoreType, Assortment, CompetitionDistance |
| Competition | CompetitionOpenMonths |

---

## API Endpoints

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `/predict-sales` | POST | Forecast daily sales for a store |
| `/predict-uplift` | POST | Measure promotion impact on sales |
| `/simulate-promotion` | POST | Calculate ROI and run/no-run recommendation |

---

## Key Findings from EDA

- Dataset contains 1,017,209 records across 1,115 stores from Jan 2013 to Jul 2015
- 172,817 rows removed where stores were closed
- Promotions drive an average 38.8% increase in daily sales
- Store Type B generates 47% more revenue than other store types
- Monday and Sunday are the strongest sales days
- The top predictive features are recent rolling sales averages, not raw lag values — meaning trend matters more than exact history

