## How to Run

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/1337dCoder/FMCG-Promo-forecast-model.git
cd FMCG-Promo-forecast-model
```

### 2. Install dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Download the dataset
Download from Kaggle: https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/rossmann-store-sales/data

Place train.csv, store.csv, test.csv into data/raw/

### 4. Run the pipelines
```bash
python pipelines/preprocess.py
python pipelines/features.py
python pipelines/train_model.py
python pipelines/explain_model.py
```

### 5. Start the API
```bash
python -m uvicorn api.main:app --reload
```

### 6. Launch the dashboard
```bash
python -m streamlit run dashboard/app.py
```

---

## Dataset

Rossmann Store Sales — Kaggle Competition
https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/rossmann-store-sales/data

1,115 Rossmann drug stores across Germany
Daily sales records from January 2013 to July 2015

